Commentary Text: Akash Madhwal to Miller, out Lbw!! Third wicket for Madhwal. And all three have been in a similar manner - batter playing across the line and being hit on the pad or losing his stump. This was the slower ball and Miller thought he could play the pull, the ball skids on and sneaks under the swinging blade, hits him on the back pad and he was right in front of middle. Madhwal has deceived GT batters by the length he's bowling. They think it is short enough but it isn't. Anyway, big wicket for MI and Rohit is pumped. Miller lbw b Akash Madhwal 41(26) [4s-4 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Chawla to Shankar, out Bowled!! Rohit in the first innings, Shankar now. Wicket right after the powerplay and timeout. Commentary Text: Akash Madhwal to Saha, out Lbw!! Oh that decision has taken everyone by surprise. The umpire's finger goes up late as he adjudicates Saha LBW. Good length on middle, Saha tries to pull but it zips under his bat to smash the front pad. Too high? No, it's clipping the bails! Will stay with umpire's call! Madhwal has been getting the ball to really skid through off the surface, and once again here it rushes after pitching. Saha lbw b Akash Madhwal 2(5)
